description.undefined: An OWL formalization of BPMN 2.0 core constructs.

comment.en: Relationship with forward/source-to-target direction (schema helper).
Activity that invokes a reusable process or global task.
Event definition that terminates the process scope immediately.
Association without arrowheads (pure annotation link).
Reusable script task definition (callable from a CallActivity).
Service operation with in/out messages and errors.
Taxonomy definition used for tagging (with categoryValues).
Diagram of participants (pools) and their message flows.
Grouping of dataOutputs that are produced together.
Property used to compute correlation keys from messages.
Expression describing how to extract a correlation property from a message.
Lists all data inputs and outputs and groups them into input/output sets.
Event that starts a process or subprocess.
Connecting object linking artifacts and flow elements (non-control).
Gateway with expression-defined merging/splitting behavior.
Connector that associates a conversation node with a participant.
Abstract element that may appear at definitions level (process, message, error, etc.).
Data assignment from source to target (within data associations).
Generic expression value (language + body).
MI behavior with no special completion rule beyond default.
A single-step interaction between participants (who sends/receives what).
Swimlane partition that groups flow nodes by responsibility.
Abstract base for event definitions (message, timer, error, etc.).
Event that waits for a trigger (base for start/intermediate-catch/boundary).
Task that sends a message.
Named escalation used by escalation events.
Connecting object that shows message exchange between participants.
Association connecting sources to a dataInput of an activity.
Configures multi-instance execution (parallel or sequential) of an activity.
Atomic unit of work.
Container grouping lanes within a process/subprocess.
AND gateway synchronizing/splitting parallel paths.
Message type (payload) referenced by operations and message flows.
Maps choreography participants to process elements.
Event that throws a trigger (base for intermediate/end throw).
Non-executable artifact (e.g., group, annotation).
Event definition for broadcast signals.
Information item that refers to a physical item (conversation context).
Event that ends a path; may throw a result (error/escalation/etc.).
Abstract base for activity looping configuration.
Named set of correlation properties to match messages to instances.
Generic performer role for an activity.
Container of flow elements; an executable or non-executable business process.
Diagram interchange rendering (icon/graphic) for an element.
Event-based gateway that waits for multiple events in parallel.
Base for nodes with incoming/outgoing sequence flows.
Abstract base for start, intermediate, end, and boundary events.
Activity that contains an embedded flow (can be expanded/collapsed).
Plain text content used in documentation/expressions.
Container for vendor/tool-specific extensions on a model element.
Mid-process event that waits for a trigger.
Embedded choreography with internal flow.
Gateway state when splitting flow (schema helper for direction).
OR gateway allowing one or more outgoing paths based on conditions.
Event definition triggered by time (date/duration/cycle).
Rule used within MI loop to control behavior on completion/activation.
Transaction focused on data persistence (non-standard specialization; diagram-level semantics).
Artifact that groups elements visually/logically.
Persistent data container shared across processes.
Defines the structure/type carried by data objects or messages.
Choreography activity repeating using standard loop semantics.
Conversation node that invokes a reusable globalConversation.
Event definition representing an error (exception).
Base for executable work (task, subprocess, callActivity).
Ad-hoc subprocess where activities may run in parallel.
Base element whose documentation/extension may include mixed content.
A pool representing a participant in collaboration.
Abstract root carrying id, documentation, and extensions.
Set of related message exchanges between participants.
Named broadcast trigger used by signal events.
Reusable conversation definition.
Gateway state when merging flow (schema helper).
Reusable abstract task definition.
Throw event without explicit marker (rarely used directly).
Choreography activity executed multiple times in parallel.
Binds a correlation property to a concrete value in a message.
Choreography activity executed multiple times sequentially.
Reference to a persistent dataStore.
Directed control-flow connection between two flow nodes, optionally with a condition.
Named state for a data object/store (e.g., Approved).
Process intended for public view/interfaces (non-executable details abstracted).
Grouping of dataInputs that are consumed together.
Ad-hoc subprocess where activities are constrained to sequential execution.
Free text attached to any model element.
Resource role specifying human execution of an activity.
Event definition signaling an escalation condition.
Association linking a conversation and model elements.
While/do-while style loop settings for an activity.
Event attached to an activity boundary (interrupting or non-interrupting).
A process describing interactions (message exchanges) between participants.
Relationship with backward/target-to-source direction (schema helper).
Parameter of a resource definition.
Abstract base for elements inside a process (activities, gateways, events, sequence flows).
Subprocess where contained activities may run in an ad-hoc (unordered/conditional) manner.
Reusable manual task definition.
Task performed by a human via a UI or worklist.
Placeholder for audit metadata of a model element.
Generic association connecting data sources and targets.
Defines an external business entity participating in conversations/choreographies.
Expression with optional language, evaluates formally (e.g., XPath, FEEL).
Abstract base for conversation, callConversation, subConversation.
Relationship with both directions (schema helper).
Associates a message flow with a message and correlation data.
Mid-process event that throws a trigger.
Gateway with unspecified direction (schema helper).
Process with type 'none' (no public/private semantics).
Base of choreographyTask and subChoreography; describes an interaction step.
Human candidate allowed to claim a user task.
Defines correlation keys subscribed to by a process for message matching.
Reference to a dataObject used in a process.
Association whose direction is both ways (diagram semantics).
Association connecting an activity's dataOutput to targets.
Lightweight data type used in conversations (non-executable informational item).
Choreography activity that calls a reusable global choreography.
Event definition that fires when a condition becomes true.
Binds a resourceParameter to a value for a specific activity.
Binds input/output parameters when calling a callable element.
Endpoint (address) used for message exchange (collaboration context).
Defines a resource (human/system) type.
Transaction marker/style for diagram rendering (non-executable, diagram-oriented).
Task that evaluates business rules/decision logic.
Task that waits to receive a message.
XOR gateway that routes one of many paths.
Event definition for sending/receiving a specific message.
Abstract base for elements that can be called (process, globalTask, globalChoreographyTask).
Gateway that routes based on the first event that occurs.
Event-based gateway that expects exactly one of several events.
One extension entry inside extensionElements.
Named error used by error events and operations.
Data artifact within a process instance.
Event definition that cancels a running transaction.
Declared input parameter for an activity/process.
Fine-grained completion/trigger rules for multi-instance behavior.
Event definition that links two points in a process (goto-like).
Task that runs an inline script.
Artifact carrying free-form explanatory text.
Role played by a partner entity in interactions.
Declares data inputs/outputs and groups of how they’re used.
Reusable user task definition.
Process internal to an organization (detailed orchestration).
Subprocess with transactional semantics (supports cancel).
Binds inputs/outputs between an activity and a callable element.
Reusable choreography task definition.
Association with direction indicated as one-way (diagram semantics).
Service interface grouping operations.
Gateway capable of both converging and diverging (schema helper).
Task performed manually without system support.
Relationship without specified direction.
Multiplicity constraints for a participant in choreography.
Transaction that triggers compensation (non-standard specialization; diagram-level semantics).
Choreography activity with no looping behavior.
MI behavior where all instances must complete per rule.
Reusable business rule task definition.
Task that invokes an automated service.
Event definition that triggers compensation handlers.
Decision/merge control point in the process flow.
Placeholder for runtime monitoring metadata of a model element.
Script body value (textual content for scriptTask, etc.).
Conversation composed of other conversation nodes.
Generic typed relationship between two model elements.
Declared output parameter for an activity/process.
MI behavior where completion is based on one instance rule.
Expression that assigns resources (performers) to an activity.
Local variable scoped to a process or flow element.
Concrete tag value from a category applied to elements.
Base role that links activities to resources/performers.
